@parilani Don't know if I'm good enough to play along to others, but maybe I'll plug in my midi whistle and try to jam along. If nothing else maybe it'll give me an idea of some new tunes to learn.
@AlexanderReind4 Unfortunately my new place is covered by trees so there's no chance of using the yard. I never really observed outside of my own yard until recently.
@AstroKatie @ryanqnorth @ebpetroff Floofs! 🐶💚
@parilani Well I'll put down my whistle so that I can listen to yall play.
@TonyJHoffman Alright, that makes much more sense. Part of me was thinking you just had 10 hours of traffic to deal with just to get out of Queens 😂

@TristanZamboni Yeah, it hasn't been good. Like tonight is mostly good for the next hour or two, but I'm not taking the risk of getting to my site only to be covered by clouds. I'm sure it'll stay clear now that I don't plan on going out.
@TonyJHoffman 22 hours? From Queens to the Adirondacks could save you 16 hours of a drive. Although the catskills would be closer.
@TristanZamboni The whole time I've had a scope (since 2010) I've had a yard to observe from. Now I don't and it's so hard to get out and enjoy the skies.
@ReineM Thanks, Reine. Hope you're doing okay!
My fellow astro folks: how many of you don't have a spot at home to setup and you have to transport your gear in order to observe?
@Hogan698 Used them all the time in math. Typically omega, epsilon, alpha, phi, lambda, and theta.

Birdies 🐦 https://t.co/SfKneNxOBT

@SiriL_Official Thank you for creating one of the best astrophotography pre processing programs. Even the post processing in this program is great, I don't really find a need for photoshop or gimp when editing images.

@GaiaSchaffner https://t.co/6ZgznvfXoE

@deepskymike Haven't seen it, but that doesn't sound very pleasing to listen to.

Also, I love lemons but never heard of frying them.
Half expected a black Friday deal at the laundromat given the amount of people that were here when I showed up.

@CraftLass @TonyJHoffman Twitter doesn't seem to have much for whistle players that I've seen. You, Tony, and one other woman I came across while searching for whistle players is all I've found. Haven't found anyone locally.
@CraftLass @TonyJHoffman Quirky stuff is the most fun stuff. I don't blame you for not having a FB account. It really is a cesspool over there.

@CraftLass @TonyJHoffman Would love to go to the Irish festival in the Catskills one of these years. I think that'd be a lot of fun.

@CraftLass @TonyJHoffman Nice!

https://t.co/y6wvuanC7l

@graffias79 I mostly removed caffeine, I have one small cup of tea in the morning and that's it. My sleep has always been horrible. Even as a kid I'd sleep for 2 or 3 hours and that would be it.

I took it 2hrs before I planned on going to sleep, & that got me a little over 8 hours between the time I wanted to sleep & when I had to wake up. I only woke up twice throughout the night, which was one more than usual, but that's because I usually wake up & then can't sleep.
RT @StargazerRob: Last night's 94% illuminated moon https://t.co/pkO1KKkB5v

I actually have a device that you put your eyepiece in, and then you put your camera on it. Used it maybe twice, but a threaded eyepiece would be much more useful I think.
